<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06128i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06128i">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06128i"> 128(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> HCE blushes / &mdash; loves sins he confesses</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Aucun de ces trompe-l&apos;oeil qui, dans nos &eacute;glises en particulier, sont comme une tentative perp&eacute;tuelle pour induire la divinit&eacute; en erreur sur la valeur de la chose offerte. Ce s&eacute;rieux, cette droiture, <mark>me faisaient rougir</mark> d&apos;avoir plus d&apos;une fois sacrifi&eacute; &agrave; un id&eacute;al moins pur. Les heures que je passais sur la colline sacr&eacute;e &eacute;taient des heures de pri&egrave;re. Toute ma vie repassait, comme une confession g&eacute;n&eacute;rale, devant mes yeux. Mais ce qu&apos;il y avait de plus singulier, c&apos;est <mark>qu&apos;en confessant mes p&eacute;ch&eacute;s, j&apos;en venais &agrave; les aimer</mark>; mes r&eacute;solutions de devenir classique finissaient par me pr&eacute;cipiter plus que jamais au p&ocirc;le oppos&eacute;. <br>[None of those trompe-l&apos;oeil that, in our churches in particular, are like an attempt perpetual to mislead the deity on the value of the thing offered. This seriousness, this righteousness, made me blush to have sacrificed more than once to a less pure ideal. The hours I spent on the sacred hill were hours of prayer. My whole life was going back, like a general confession, before my eyes. But the most singular thing was that by confessing my sins, I came to like them; my resolutions of becoming better ended by precipitating myself more than ever at the opposite pole. <small> Ernest Renan, <a name="ERSD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ERSD"><cite title="source">Souvenirs d'enfance et de jeunesse</cite></a> (1883) 62</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01180i" href="c01all.htm#c01180i">VI.C.01:180(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
